{
  "stem": "18102.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father had done the right thing, once again and didn't return.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we didn't know where he was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when the NKVD came, they said as soon as we hear from him, be sure to tell them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, my mother agreed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, of course, she didn't know how she would hear from him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because you must remember, we didn't have a telephone.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] eventually-- I mean, maybe semaphore, but we didn't know how.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was a worrisome time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then suddenly one evening Mrs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "London-- that was her name, a friend who lived nearby-- came rushing to the house.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She had a telephone in her house, because they, they had a store.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my father was on the phone.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my mother left with her, rushing to answer the phone call and returned an hour or so later, having talked with my father.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she told me that he was OK and that he had learned that Stalin was gonna give Vilna over to the Lithuanians.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Vilna had always been on the cusp between Lithuania and Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there was a tug-of-war, always, about Vilna, the city, whether it was really Lithuanian or whether it was really Polish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And Stalin, in his magnanimity, was giving Vilna up, once again, to the Lithuanians, as it turned out, only for a little while.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But nevertheless, that meant that Vilna would fall under the Lithuanian rule and not Russian rule.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my father felt safer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Therefore it was agreed between him and my mother that we would take, that evening, the train out of Bialystok, because the border would be closed the following morning when this eventuality happened.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
